1. In Java, the `HashSet` only allows for unique elements, so adding a list to a `HashSet` directly will result in duplicates. Using the `addAll` method on a `HashSet` is not recommended as it violates the invariant of `HashSet`. Here is the correct way to add a list to a `HashSet`:

